The paper discusses a system for enhancing software security through software diversity techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The system is distributed across multiple heterogeneous hosts, which involves issues related to distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses performance challenges and solutions, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the system involves differences in hardware security features, which could potentially fall under the category of architecture (cs.AR).
